msgid "Getting Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:5
# 38c9c4e7f8fe4e8d8c5355330a084227
msgid "One Laptop per Child is an education project, not a laptop project. With connected laptops, learners are liberated to actively engage with others with similar interests in cultures of learning by doing without being limited by time or space. If you are having hardware or software problems with your XO, remember that its design is to encourage you to learn new things by trying to solve problems on your own!"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:7
# 304b091d19bf456b872a23dcbcc3c280
msgid "That said, an entire community built this XO and everything on it, and we want to help you with it. Our OLPC global community of volunteers provide software and hardware troubleshooting and support. This section will help tell you where to find Support when you are really stuck! OLPC has proven that volunteer-driven support works, often with far more heartfelt caring than any corporate help desk!"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:9
# d600fefbc4c44710a64e72df98c099d3
msgid "If you have questions about the XO, ask a teacher for help, a friend, or search on the Internet. If you have a question about your XO, there is a very good chance it is already answered within our expanding Support FAQ / RTFM knowledge base:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:11
# 44697a87ea12449588635169a9a0605e
msgid "http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Support_FAQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:13
# 5db5b98281fd423bbcb66fd38a3bc612
msgid "Next try looking at http://support.laptop.org extensive helpful guidance for exploring and fixing your XO, allowing you to solve challenging issues right alongside others. Specifically, check out:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:15
# 925380237eca418baabff83ca3769d28
msgid "Getting Started: http://laptop.org/start"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:17
# df00acc5d65d4025b801bc5741134823
msgid "Email Lists: http://lists.laptop.org"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:19
# 4f8426bdb59147d8b87f38a9608df09b
msgid "Live Chat: http://forum.laptop.org/chat"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:21
# 75da90f86e3a483a892ceca733d210a1
msgid "OLPC Community: Wiki http://wiki.laptop.org"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:23
# e05e1056f1b44f9cb3d55e7e0d6ffe74
msgid "If you are still unable to find an answer online, please email help@laptop.org."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:25
# 2f64fc8ab91344288548309831e36dad
msgid "Did you know that our volunteers staff a live Help Chat site 24/7, on the Internet? Click here: http://forum.laptop.org/chat Login with the color-name shown; that's guest ID. Type your question in the chat line at the bottom. You may have to wait for a response as our volunteers come in and out. If you are patient, we can probably help you! To learn more about what Internet Relay Chat (the system that makes this possible) is, click here: http://wiki.laptop.org/go/IRC"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:27
# 020091054d35442d9409a275a409a4f9
msgid "We would also like to make special mention of our Support Gang, where an enthusiastic group of volunteers assist XO users all over the world. If you are impressed with the passion and hard work of our volunteers, please consider giving back, by joining our dedicated community. Take a look at the link below. We would welcome your participation! http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Support_Gang http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Support_FAQ Be sure to review the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) link above. Many of us join and \"learn by doing.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../source/getting_support.rst:29
